ABOUT THE ROLE

Are you passionate about leveraging artificial intelligence to make a meaningful impact? We are seeking an experienced Senior Business Analyst who will play a critical role in triaging AI-related requests, supporting the AI Ethics and Advisory Committee, and leading cutting-edge AI experimentation initiatives. This dynamic position offers the opportunity to collaborate with talented colleagues, tackle complex challenges, and shape the future of responsible AI development.




Key responsibilities:

Collaborate and partner with a wide range of stakeholders to understand business needs, build strong relationships, and ensure alignment of AI initiatives with organisational goals.
Efficiently triage and prioritise AI requests from various stakeholders, ensuring timely and effective resolution.
Provide technical and strategic support to the AI Ethics and Advisory Committee, contributing to policy development and ethical decision-making.
Lead experimentation and pilot projects in AI and machine learning, driving innovation and continuous improvement.
Communicate complex technical concepts clearly to diverse audiences, fostering understanding and engagement.




ABOUT YOU

You possess the drive, passion, and determination to set your own vision and strive to make a meaningful impact. You will be partnering with a variety of stakeholders to build strong relationships and ensure alignment with organisational goals. You have a strong problem-solving mindset, excellent communication skills, and the ability to embrace challenges. Additionally, you are committed to upholding ethical standards in AI and promoting responsible innovation.  To be successful in this role you will also demonstrate:

5+ years driving impactful AI and IT projects as a Senior Business Analyst in dynamic, cross-functional teams
Leading or contributing to AI projects
Proficiency with Jira and Confluence
Exceptional written and verbal communication
Desired: Proficiency in SDLC, Test Development Lifecycle, and agile methodologies.

 

ABOUT US

Chartered Accountants Australia and New Zealand (CA ANZ) represents more than 140,000 financial professionals, supporting them to make a meaningful difference in the communities where they work and live. We are committed to advancing the profession through high ethical standards, world-class education, and advocacy for the public good. Guided by our purpose and values, we aspire to be a magnet for diverse talent, equip our members for success, and lead the way in sustainability, innovation, and trust in business and finance.




WHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU

At CA ANZ, we are committed to creating a workplace that reflects our values of collaboration, integrity, diversity, and accountability. As part of our strategy to be a magnet for diverse talent and an adaptive, member-centric organisation, we offer:




A strong focus on equity, diversity, and inclusion embedded in everything we do
Opportunities to grow your career through inspiring learning and development pathways
A flexible hybrid work model that balances autonomy with the benefits of in-person collaboration
A culture that values your voice and empowers you to make an impact in your community and profession
Grow your skills and future with unlimited access to LinkedIn learning
The chance to contribute to meaningful work that creates real impact for people across Aotearoa and Australia







HOW TO APPLY

Simply select APPLY NOW and submit your application today. Applications close Tuesday, 10 February 2026.




CA ANZ welcomes applications from people of all ages, genders, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, Māori, Pasifika, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with a disability, and people who are diverse in gender and sexuality.

Perpetual Group is an ASX-listed company (ASX:PPT) headquartered in Sydney, Australia, currently consisting of 11 leading brands across three distinct businesses: Asset Management, Wealth Management and Corporate Trust.

Perpetual Asset Management is a global multi-boutique asset management business offering an extensive range of specialist investment capabilities through seven boutiques and brands in key regions globally. Within Australia, Perpetual and Pendal have a broad range of capabilities across Australian and global equities, credit, fixed income, multi-asset and ESG. We have a growing presence in the US, UK and Europe through our brands Barrow Hanley, Trillium, JO Hambro, Regnan, and TSW.

About the role

As a Senior Analyst, Investment Analytics, you will play a critical role in delivering accurate, timely and insightful performance and attribution reporting across a broad range of asset classes. You'll provide technical oversight, act as a subject matter expert on complex attribution matters and support continuous improvement across the Investment Analytics function.

This 12-month max term contract role offers significant exposure to portfolio managers and senior stakeholders and is well suited to someone who enjoys combining technical expertise with collaboration, problem‑solving and mentoring.


Key Responsibilities:

Deliver daily and monthly performance and attribution reporting across equity, fixed income, diversified and absolute return strategies.
Provide daily fixed income and equity attribution analysis to portfolio managers, with clear and concise explanations.
Complete month‑end performance, attribution and ad‑hoc reporting requests.
Act as a subject matter expert on complex attribution queries and present insights to senior stakeholders.
Identify operational issues early and resolve or escalate appropriately.
Manage data flows across holdings, pricing, benchmarks, corporate actions and analytics outputs.
Work effectively with IBOR and ABOR data structures and custodial feeds.
Support BAU delivery through strong governance, controls and data quality processes.
Build risk knowledge to support cross‑training with the Investment Risk team.
Provide technical guidance and support to junior analysts.

What We're Looking For:

Degree qualification (preferred).
CFA and/or CIPM qualifications beneficial.
5+ years' experience in performance measurement or investment analytics.
Proven experience delivering performance and attribution reporting under time‑critical deadlines.
Strong understanding of fixed income performance drivers, including carry, roll‑down, duration, curve, spreads, FX and inflation‑linked analytics.
Ability to interpret and clearly explain analytics to portfolio managers and non‑technical stakeholders.
Advanced Excel, Power Query, Power BI and SQL skills.
Strong experience with FactSet performance and analytics modules.
Experience working with IBOR vs ABOR data and custodial feeds.
Exposure to investment risk frameworks desirable.
Demonstrated ability to leverage digital tools and emerging analytics capabilities to improve efficiency and insights.
Strong risk awareness and commitment to regulatory and internal governance standards.


How we work


Our unique culture is underpinned by our three organisational behaviours, Stretch, Own it, Make an impact which drive our approach of day-to-day interactions with colleagues and clients, the way we approach decision-making to the questions we ask and the problems we solve.


Employee benefits

We're committed to creating an inclusive workplace where diversity is celebrated. No matter your background or circumstances, we aim to provide an environment where you can thrive.

As our highly valued Manager, Credit Risk Analytics based in Brisbane you will bring your strong analytical skills to support the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, to execute the credit risk optimisation strategy for Great Southern Bank.

Working with key partners and internal stakeholders, you will pro-actively manage critical quantitative models and tools used in the origination and management of the bank's retail lending products (Home Loans, Credit Cards and Personal Loans) in a way that balances growth, customer experience and credit risk.

You'll make an impact by:

Leadership

You are accountable in supporting the development of a credit risk strategy that supports the bank's strategic objectives across its key portfolios and customer segments and assisting in the articulation of that strategy with senior leaders, executives, directors and regulators.
You will provide thought leadership across teams including Risk, Products, Projects and Data to influence effective design and delivery of leading loan origination pathways.

Credit Risk

In conjunction with the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, you will design automated decisioning acquisition strategies and models to support existing and new products.
Using robust credit risk management techniques you will ensure the credit risk models and tools are designed in line with our Model Risk framework including appropriate monitoring and review that drives continuous improvement. This will include monitoring outcomes and performance, application of quantitative techniques, professional credit risk judgement, engagement with internal senior stakeholders and external partners, forums and regulators.
You will maintain and monitor the data and reporting for our credit risk tools and provide succinct summaries to the executive and credit committees. You will thrive for continuous improvement across credit risk models, tools and practices.
You will leverage your colleagues in the Credit Risk team, supporting each other with insights and professional opinions to drive outcomes across credit oversight, policy and loan decisioning tools.

Reporting, Analysis and Insights

You will develop and design regular reporting and analysis relating to application trends, new originations, and portfolio.
You will design and deliver reporting and insights that helps ensure the Board is able to fulfil its obligations for oversight of the lending portfolios.
You will support recurring and ad hoc quantitative analysis to ensure portfolio health is understood and to identify opportunities to better manage risk-return.
You may be required to support ongoing management of the provision model, including reporting as well reviewing and validating the model remains fit for purpose.
You may be required to conduct portfolio stress testing to further support credit insights and to contribute to enterprise stress testing and ICAAP.

Systems and partners

You will have dual responsibility for the execution and risk management of credit risk strategy, including design, business requirements, test planning and execution, model governance, data requirements etc.
You will work closely with technology platform owners and business owners to prioritise delivery of credit risk solutions into those platforms.

Partners and stakeholders

You will work the Senior Manager, Credit Strategy, Product Managers, Data and Technology partners and the management of our key external risk partners including but not limited to mortgage insurance, credit bureaux, valuation and scorecard providers and validators.



Do things differently with us

To succeed in this role, you will have:

5+ years' experience in credit risk management roles within Financial Services
Strong understanding of commonly used credit tools and decision engines and how to create the best value through their use
Proficient with data extraction, manipulation, and analysis (DataBricks and or SQL is essential).
Strong communication and stakeholder management skills
Familiarity with the Australian market, regulations (APRA, ASIC, AFCA)

Why Great Southern Bank?

Whatever your role with us, you'll be part of a force for good. We're owned by our customers right here in Australia, so our success benefits everyday people and families. Working at Great Southern Bank, you'll also enjoy a range of fantastic benefits, some examples include:

About the role

FinCap Australia is seeking an Investment Analyst, Portfolio & Investment Solutions to support the continued build and scale of our Private Asset Managed Account (PAMA) platform.

Reporting directly to the Head of Portfolio & Investment Solutions, this is a hands on analytical role within the investment function, supporting portfolio design, manager research, due diligence and ongoing monitoring across private markets. The role contributes directly to the quality, governance and scalability of portfolio solutions delivered to advisers and clients.

The position is full time and based in Melbourne, with Sydney-based candidates considered.

What you’ll be doing

Support the Head of Portfolio & Investment Solutions with research, analysis and implementation across private asset portfolios

Conduct detailed due diligence across private equity, private credit, real assets and infrastructure strategies

Prepare investment reports, market scans and peer comparisons to support portfolio and product selection

Analyse performance, attribution and liquidity data sourced from external managers

Support scenario analysis, stress testing and liquidity modelling across model portfolios

Assist with the preparation of quarterly reports, presentations and client materials

Maintain investment datasets and reporting frameworks to support transparency and governance

Coordinate with fund managers, custodians and platform providers to obtain performance and compliance data

Support the ongoing monitoring of investments and portfolio implementation within platform structures

Work closely with Treasury and Client Partnerships teams to support platform delivery

What we’re looking for

3 to 7 years’ experience in investment consulting, funds research or manager research

Experience in private markets, particularly real estate, private equity or private credit, is an advantage

Strong analytical and financial modelling skills, with confidence handling large datasets

Experience preparing investment research, reports or formal investment documentation

Tertiary qualifications in finance, economics or a related discipline

Postgraduate study or professional qualifications such as CFA, CAIA or FINSIA highly regarded

Understanding of portfolio analytics and investment governance processes is desirable

What we offer

You will join a growing private markets platform at a formative stage, working closely with senior investment leadership and gaining direct exposure to portfolio construction, private asset research and platform development. A competitive remuneration package will be offered, commensurate with experience.

About FinCap

FinCap is a specialist private markets investment firm focused on delivering disciplined access, governance and portfolio solutions for advisers and wholesale investors. Through our Private Asset Managed Account (PAMA) platform, we are building scalable infrastructure to support investment across private equity, private credit and real assets.

About Us

Rabobank is the world’s leading specialist in food & agribusiness banking.  One of our key strengths lies in our people who have a deep understanding of agriculture & are committed to adding long-term value for clients.  Our commitment to our employees & clients is at the heart of everything we do.   

About the Role

Rabobank’s COO Domain’s Regulatory Reporting & Data Quality Team is responsible for managing & ensuring the accuracy of regulatory reporting (FATCA/CRS/AIIR/annual statements etc).  The team has an opening in Sydney for a 12-month fixed term contract for a Senior Regulatory Reporting Analyst.

Reporting to Senior Manager Regulatory Reporting & Data Quality, this role will initially support the implementation of CRS 2.0 starting with New Zealand as the first focus, followed by Australia.  This is hands-on discovery & analysis work - ideal for someone who is naturally inquisitive & enjoys unpacking how reports are structured end-to-end.  You will work to understand the story behind the data, map processes, & analyse the impact of regulatory change on existing reporting & processes.

Top Role Accountabilities: 

Assessing regulatory changes & analysing the impact on current reporting through impact assessment

Identifying additional data or business-rule changes required for regulatory reporting

Gathering, analysing, & documenting business requirements related to regulatory reporting

Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:


Be part of a team that develops, deploys, supports, and modernises a proprietary business critical system.
Take on a key role in a significant redevelopment of this system that requires strong C++ and software design capability
Join a collaborative group that values curiosity, problem solving, and thoughtful engineering



The opportunity to join our team

We are looking for a Senior Analyst Engineer who enjoys solving complex problems, thrives in environments with uncertainty, and is ready for a new challenge. This team owns a proprietary system that is central to the business, and we are responsible for its end-to-end development, ongoing support, and continuous modernisation. A major focus over the coming period is a significant redevelopment of this system. This work involves architectural redesign, complex problem solving, and deep C++ engineering.

In this role you will work across development, production support, testing, and broader IT tasks, with the balance of work evolving over time based on system needs and team priorities. Flexibility, openness, and curiosity are key.

This is a great opportunity for someone who wants to apply their senior level software engineering expertise, contribute to a major area of system development, and play an influential role within a highly collaborative team.

What you will be doing
In this role you will work across a mix of development, support, and system improvement activities, contributing to both day to day outcomes and longer term engineering uplift.

Designing, developing, and delivering changes to business-critical systems using C++ and modern software design principles
Playing a central role in the upcoming system redevelopment, including rearchitecting components and solving complex technical challenges
Working closely with architects, delivery leads, technical specialists, and business partners to shape and implement quality solutions
Supporting production environments on a rotating roster to maintain system reliability and availability
Building deep knowledge of the unit pricing system and its broader ecosystem
Uplifting system capability and engineering practices across the team
Providing informal mentoring by sharing your technical strengths, explaining your reasoning clearly, and influencing decision making in positive ways
Helping shape a constructive, energetic, and supportive team culture

What You Bring to This Role
We are looking for someone who brings strong engineering capability, a positive mindset, and the confidence to operate in evolving and sometimes uncertain technical environments.

Strong C++ software development experience (ideally 8 or more years, but we are flexible for the right capability)
Strong software design skills and experience working in complex systems
Comfortable operating in technical ambiguity and taking ownership in uncertain situations
Someone who wants variety in their work and is open to the mix of responsibilities evolving over time
A proactive approach to problem solving with the ability to work independently when required
Clear communication skills and the ability to explain technical decisions in a way that helps others learn
A positive influence who brings energy, patience, and a willingness to help the team grow
Experience across cloud environments, DevOps practices, Linux, SQL, or scripting is beneficial but not required

Industry background is open. What matters most is your engineering capability, your mindset, and your appetite for challenge.

Find the better way

What gets us excited about working here? Helping people feel good about their money as one of Australia's leading financial wellbeing organisations. From those starting out to those retiring. As your team, we'll show up for you and together we will create financial wellbeing for every Australian. Because we know people who are confident about their financial future live better lives.

If this sounds like your kind of career, you sound like our kind of person. With us, you'll do work that builds your technical know-how and challenges our entire industry to move forward. Along the way, you'll be free to explore new ideas and technology, solve problems in a team, and independently to get great things done. Around here, we like to call it "putting our fingerprints on the future".

People-inspired tech
